<h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Since OVO 8.16, the virtual addresses of HA packages are
ignored when establishing whether the message node is local or not. This means&nbsp;<span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"># opcmsg a=a o=o msg_t=t
node=&lt;explicit_virtual_hostname&gt;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">is treated as a proxied message. Before 8.16, these messages
were marked as local (not-proxied) and added to the physical node when writing
them to the DB. Therefore the messages were ignored for the service tree of the
virtual host and the status calculation not correct. If this variable is set to
TRUE, the virtual IP address is taken into account and the pre-OVO 8.16
behavior is achieved.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Brief overview of direct messages and proxied messages
generated by opcmsga<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Proxied message means the message does not belong to the
local node.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Example:</p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>O<span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">n a node named test.testnode.com we send a message with
node="test2.testnode.com" then message is marked as proxied and it
gets mapped to test2.testnode.com in OM side though it is generated from
test.testnode.com.</span></li><li>The message with node="test.testnode.com" then
message is marked as "Direct" i.e. belongs to local node where
message is generated.</li><li>Proxied messages play a big role in snmp traps as traps are
generated from remote node and processed by opctrapi running on some other node.</li><li>OMW side mapping of message onto a node</li><li>It always depends which message properties are set in the
incoming message.</li></ul><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">For non-proxied messages this works as follows:<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>If agentId (alias core is of managed node) is contained in
the message then the message is validated by using the agentID. </li><li>If agentID is not contained then the validation is more
complex:</li><li>If node name is set but no agent id then validation is based
on the node name</li><li>If ip is set only then validation is based in ip address</li><li>If both node name and ip is set then the validation checks
whether node name maps to ip and ip maps to node name, if yes it is validated
whether node is configured in OMW's node bank</li></ul><o:p></o:p><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">For proxied messages this works as follows:<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>It will be checked whether they contain the agentID of the
proxied node (besides the ip address).</li><li>Then by setting a configuration value it can be configured
whether the proxied node should be validated as a configured managed node and
then the real managed node will&nbsp; be
validated by it's IP address. </li><li>If agentID of the proxied node is not set then the
validation is done by using the ip-address of the managed node.</li><li>By default opcmsga queries the ip interfaces and retrieves
the configured ip addresses in the system, from this list the virtual ip addresses
are ignored. But when OPC_INCLUDE_VIRTUAL_IP_ADDRS_FOR_LOCAL_NODE_MAPPING is
set to TRUE the virtual ip address are included in the list. This ip address
list maintained by opcmsga is used for determining if a message generated is
Direct one or Proxied one.</li></ul><o:p></o:p><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Few end user scenarios where this config variable could be
used:<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>One scenario is to disable opcmsga retrieving virtual ip
addresses during startup this variable can be used. </li><li>Another scenario in combination with OPC_SET_PROXY_FLAG_FOR_IP_ADDRESSES
variable it can be used for the below mentioned scenario.<br>eg: Set OPC_IP_ADDRESS to virtual ip address. In that
scenario messages associated with that virtual ip address is marked Direct
instead of Proxied. To work around that OPC_SET_PROXY_FLAG_FOR_IP_ADDRESSES can
be set to the virtual ip address.</li></ul><div><h2>OPC_STORE_TIME_FOR_MGR_INFO</h2><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
 <tbody><tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-width: 1pt; border-left-style: solid; border-color: black; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span lang="EN-US" style=""><b>Type</b></span><span lang="EN-US" style=""><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top-width: 1pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-top-color: black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-left: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span lang="EN-US" style="">Integer<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span lang="EN-US" style=""><b>Default Value</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: black; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: black; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span lang="EN-US" style="">24
  (in hours)<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span lang="EN-US" style=""><b>Class of the
  variable</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>
