<h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">OPC_STORE_TIME_FOR_MGR_INFO config variable is used to set
maximum time a message operation info block is held in the message agent.<o:p></o:p></p>

<h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Message Agent (opcmsga) process provides the interface for
sending messages, action responses, message operations to the management
server.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">The processed messages/action responses that are to be sent
to the server are written into the msgagtdf file. If the OM Server is not
reachable it periodically tries to connect a target system. If it connects,
message-agent sends the buffered data.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">In msgagtdf buffer file messages are not cleared but are
overwritten as needed. This can result in fragmentation in the file. Opcmsga
process by default clean defragment/cleanup the file every 24 hours.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Possible scenarios where OPC_STORE_TIME_FOR_MGR_INFO
variable could be used:</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Opcmsga process store the buffer message up to 2 GB. If it
reaches more than that opcmsga fails to process the message and forward the message
to Management server. <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">To Overcome the situation, we can use config variable
OPC_STORE_TIME_FOR_MGR_INFO, we can change the interval in hours with which
opcmsga process defragment/cleanup the file.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Special Case:</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">If OPC_STORE_TIME_FOR_MGR_INFO config variable is set to 20.
The opcmsga process cleanup buffer file every 20 minutes. This is can be set if
the number of outgoing message is too high and buffer file msgagtdf size is too
high.<o:p></o:p></p></div><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p></div><o:p></o:p><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

